==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sciolist
<hw>Sci"o*list</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>sciolus</ets>. See <er>Sciolous</er>.]</ety> <def>One who knows
many things superficially; a pretender to science; a
smatterer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>These passages in that book were enough to humble the presumption
of our modern <qex>sciolists</qex>, if their pride were not as great as
their ignorance.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W. Temple.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A master were lauded and <qex>sciolists</qex> shent.</q>
<rj><qau>R. Browning.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sciolistic</ent>⟦br⟧
